Heat oven to 375 degrees F. Rinse chicken inside and out with cold water; pat dry with paper towels. Place in shallow baking pan. Brush butter over outside of chicken; sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of the rub. Sprinkle remaining rub inside chicken. Place orange and onion pieces inside chicken. Secure legs and wings. Bake 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours or until leg twists easily in socket, and chicken is no longer pink in the center.